timber and Corten steel offer a tactile warmth that complements the adjacent greenhouse and surrounding greenery. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-05.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. \" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-05.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-05-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-05-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-05-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-05-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-05-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eA living wall and green roof further integrate the structure into the landscape, while expansive glazing transforms the pavilion into a light-filled observatory of passing time.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-06.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. \" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-06.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-06-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-06-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-06-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-06-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-06-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe interplay of light and texture is key. Carefully placed architectural and task lighting accentuate colors and contrasts, while natural light shifts throughout the day to create a dynamic interior experience.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-07.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. \" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-07.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-07-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-07-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-07-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-07-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-07-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-08.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. \" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-08.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-08-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-08-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-08-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-08-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-08-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eInside, the design reflects the client’s global sensibility and deep appreciation for music and art. Custom joinery doubles as both display and storage, housing a curated collection of artifacts with museum-like precision. Metal mesh panels and track lighting subtly frame each piece, offering depth and dimension without overwhelming the space.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-09.jpg\" alt=\"The interior of this modern music pavilion is a refined blend of sound-focused design and artful display, featuring custom joinery, soft lighting, and a cascading glass pendant that reflects like ripples across the minimalist micro cement floor.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-09.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-09-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-09-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-09-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-09-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe mood is minimal yet immersive, with grey micro cement floors forming a neutral base for layered textures and color. Wall lighting by Holly Hunt adds softness, while a showstopping pendant light installation by Wonderglass hovers overhead like ripples on water—its reflections playing across the surfaces below.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"2400\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-10.jpg\" alt=\"The interior of this modern music pavilion is a refined blend of sound-focused design and artful display, featuring custom joinery, soft lighting, and a cascading glass pendant that reflects like ripples across the minimalist micro cement floor.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-10.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-10-940x1175.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-10-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-10-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-10-1229x1536.jpg 1229w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-10-1638x2048.jpg 1638w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1896\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-11.jpg\" alt=\"The interior of this modern music pavilion is a refined blend of sound-focused design and artful display, featuring custom joinery, soft lighting, and a cascading glass pendant that reflects like ripples across the minimalist micro cement floor.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-11.jpg 1896w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-11-940x1269.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-11-800x1080.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-11-768x1037.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-11-1138x1536.jpg 1138w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-11-1517x2048.jpg 1517w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1896px) 100vw, 1896px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe pavilion isn’t just beautiful, it’s engineered for listening. Achieving exceptional acoustic isolation and quality meant consulting with specialists to fine-tune the proportions, materials, and even service buffering. Every element, from the geometry of the room to the placement of absorptive materials, was considered in pursuit of sonic perfection.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-12.jpg\" alt=\"The interior of this modern music pavilion is a refined blend of sound-focused design and artful display, featuring custom joinery, soft lighting, and a cascading glass pendant that reflects like ripples across the minimalist micro cement floor.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-12.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-12-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-12-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-12-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-12-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAudio-visual integration was led by \u003ca href=\"https://ideaworks.co.uk\"\u003eIdeaworks\u003c/a\u003e, who helped unite lighting, sound, shading, and environmental controls. Together with SHH, they delivered a space that functions effortlessly and invisibly, with features like concealed blinds, ASHP energy-efficient heating, and intelligent climate systems all working behind the scenes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1690\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-13.jpg\" alt=\"The interior of this modern music pavilion is a refined blend of sound-focused design and artful display, featuring custom joinery, soft lighting, and a cascading glass pendant that reflects like ripples across the minimalist micro cement floor.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-13.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-13-940x827.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-13-800x704.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-13-768x676.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-13-1536x1352.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eThis Music Pavilion goes beyond its original brief. Though designed for music, it also invites work, reflection, and relaxation. It’s a modern temple to personal expression, where architecture, interiors, and acoustics work in concert.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-14.jpg\" alt=\"The interior of this modern music pavilion is a refined blend of sound-focused design and artful display, featuring custom joinery, soft lighting, and a cascading glass pendant that reflects like ripples across the minimalist micro cement floor.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-14.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-14-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-14-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-14-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-14-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-14-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eFrom textured materials to immersive soundscapes, every detail has been crafted for impact. The result is a building that’s not only visually and sonically rich but deeply personal, a true extension of the client’s lifestyle, passions, and artistic vision.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-15.jpg\" alt=\"The interior of this modern music pavilion is a refined blend of sound-focused design and artful display, featuring custom joinery, soft lighting, and a cascading glass pendant that reflects like ripples across the minimalist micro cement floor.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-15.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-15-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-15-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-15-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAt night, the pavilion transforms into a glowing sculptural form. Discreet exterior lighting highlights the charred timber cladding and Corten steel details, casting shadows that accentuate the building’s geometry. The warm illumination enhances the natural textures while allowing the pavilion to gently emerge from the landscape, creating an inviting presence after dark without overpowering its surroundings.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-16.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. At night, subtle lighting brings the textures to life, softly illuminating its bold architectural form.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-16.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-16-940x627.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-16-800x533.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-16-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-16-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"2400\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-17.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. At night, subtle lighting brings the textures to life, softly illuminating its bold architectural form.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-17.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-17-940x1175.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-17-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-17-768x960.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-17-1229x1536.jpg 1229w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-17-1638x2048.jpg 1638w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1920\" height=\"2074\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-18.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. At night, subtle lighting brings the textures to life, softly illuminating its bold architectural form.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-18.jpg 1920w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-18-940x1015.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-18-800x864.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-18-768x830.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-18-1422x1536.jpg 1422w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-18-1896x2048.jpg 1896w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1708\" height=\"2560\" src=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-19.jpg\" alt=\"This modern music pavilion blends charred timber, Corten steel, and a living roof to create a sculptural retreat in the landscape. At night, subtle lighting brings the textures to life, softly illuminating its bold architectural form.\" srcset=\"https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-19.jpg 1708w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-19-940x1409.jpg 940w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-19-800x1199.jpg 800w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-19-768x1151.jpg 768w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-19-1025x1536.jpg 1025w, https://www.contemporist.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/private-music-pavilion-room-architecture-design-260625-1244-19-1366x2048.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1708px) 100vw, 1708px\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWatch the following video to learn more about this project from everyone involved.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ciframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EAcUrYsgAgE\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"\u003e\u003c/iframe\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhether filled with music, art, or quiet reflection, the pavilion offers a space that feels both grounded and elevated, a place where every detail resonates.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003chr/\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch6\u003ePhotography by \u003ca href=\"https://www.rchivers.co.uk/\"\u003eRichard Chivers\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h6\u003e\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
